>Hmm... I must not understand something here... Why is there a big increase
>from 4-5 bitplanes??
>
>The way I understand it:
>
>	4 to 5:		25 % increase in rendering costs. 
>
>	16 to 32: 	100 % increase in colors.
>
>If this is true, it seems like a good deal to me...
>
>Hmmm... Well, now that I think about, if the 5 bitplanes are really 
>taking up all the bandwidth, that would limit how much rendering one
>could do...
>
>Perhaps someone who is knowledgable could go into more depth...

Well it's not really going directly from 4 to 5 planes that kills it.. rendering an extra plane is not what slows things down, rather the DMA overhead when you have 5 bitplanes or more on a standard chipset machine.  Same thing.. (except worse) happens 
hen you go to hires screen in 4 bpls.  So the rendering cost
in actuality is MUCH higher than 25% increase.  The nice thing about AGA is
that the DMA bandwidth was increased and so this problem no longer exists...
so your processor can be going full speed, your blitter can be running
unhindered and you can still jam in lots of copper instructions per line :)

