That docking computer is a real stupid bitch in 68000 Amigas, it's way
too slow, and it almost always destroys your ship, if you want to see
the operation at real time.

Here's what to do. After you have entered from hyperspace, click F2
two times. Pick the EXACT target for autopilot where to go now. So,
zoom in enough so that you can see the space station or city or what-
ever. 

(hint: shift+(double-?)clicking zoom_in icon (or F6?) rules).

Now, hit the autopilot on (F7), and use the Maximum ">>>>>" time
acceleration (SHIFT+F5). Don't do a THING until you reach the target.

* When you come close to a SPACE STATION, computer will set the time
scale to realtime ">". Hit ">>" gadget. This prevents the usual crashes
when docking.

* When you come close to a CITY/PLANET, don't do a thing. Don't use
time scale buttons. They'll make you sometimes crash - not always, 
though. 

...and suddenly, the Frontier is a pretty nice game again. :)

-Fernis, btw - I've seen the PC/486-Frontier. AWESOME!!! Texture-bitmaps
               are not slow as I had guessed. Amiga-version looks in fact
               quite awful compared to 486. (ok, using 68000 in comparison). 

