Oh, how true those words are!  I'd have to say that one of the Amiga's
biggest problems (if not *the* biggest) is that all games cater for the
lowest common denominator.  It's like PC game writers writing *all* games
to work on an XT and if it works on the better machines, then thats a bonus.

