  Ok, you now own Frontier.  And its huge, you have little idea of what to do
and less idea how to get rich.  Well read on. 
  If you don't want any help with this game then skip this post. :)
  In the beginning.  It is easiest to start at Ross 154, the autopilot makes
life much simpler.  Load up with animal meat and take the mission to Bernard's
star.  From there go to Sol carring robots.  As your pulse laser is next to
useless sell it and outfit your ship with two Naval missiles.  As they are
immune to ECM and can chase a target for over 300km they outperform your
pitiful laser.  Keep moving stuff back and forth between Sol and Bernard's
Star for a while.  When you can afford a Military 1 Drive get it, it takes up
half as much space as the normal one, now you have to use military fuel.  Be
careful, when used it becomes radioactives, which are illegal in the Sol
system.  Get in the habit of dumping it after every jump and refuel.  And
since you are moving between two space stations you can sell your atmospheric
shielding to give you extra space.  From Sol carry Luxury Goods back to
Bernard's star, and taking any missions going your way.  Eventually you will
have enough to upgrade your ship, a good step up would be the Viper, as it can
carry missiles and has a decent cargo capacity.  Fit it with a 1MW Beam Laser
and you are now ready for some real combat.
  Dogfight Tactics.  Learn to use your autopilot for aiming.  Target your
opponent, hitting escape and pausing the game makes this easier.  Turn on your
autopilot when your opponent is a ways away from your say at least 3km.  Any
closer and you risk a colision.  Be careful, when you are lined up like this
your opponent is also, so save the game before fights.  A good way to get that
3km is to fire a missile at your opponent.  The naval missiles I reccomend may
be enough to kill your target, but given enough lead and speed they can be
outrun.  So when your opponent comes back in you should be facing him already,
just leave the autopilot on and start firing at about 5-6km away.  Bigger and
slower opponents you can kill with manual aiming, but always keep at least 300
kph speed set, any slower and you become an easy target.  You can aim much
easier if you turn off your engines, but you will have a tendency to get
rammed by opponents.  So the lesson is, chase them off with a missile, if they
live through that then laser them on the way back.
  Smuggling.  You can make a lot of credits carrying contraband, but unless
you are going to cheat and save the game right before you dock, say in the
last 2km or so, and reload if you get fined, it won't be worth it.  A word of
advice though.  Any system that has contraband for sale will have plenty of
pirates in it.  So be prepared for combat on the way to the port.  You may
want to carry extra fuel in case you run into too much opposition.  He who
fights and runs away, lives.  The viper gives you 4 missiles and the beam
laser, it should be enough though.  And killing all those pirates is good for
your Elite rating.

  Hope this helps someone.

