>>> -- 
>	But those PC owners will have a 256 col version with texture mapping
>and a really good intro and have sampled speech......Still it probably takes 20
>megs of HD space!!!!
>	If there is an AGA version wont it be very slow on the 1200 with only
>2megs of chip RAM????? 

   Nope. Optimizing for 68020+ 32-bit machines makes a really HUGE difference.
One thing comes to mind when I say that. Tmapdemo - by Chris Green. There are
others, but there are two things you can cancel out here. 1. Calculations
per cycle are done faster with bigger words and optimizations so you get
your needed punch for 3D. 
    2. AGA machines wouldn't really be hindered much by using 256-color
screens as ECS with 32. This is especially true if they used 128-color
screens with 7 bitplanes. When people want even more speed, they use
the 128-color option. Not surehow much difference it makes, but any addition
of speed without the ability to see the difference between 7 or 8 bitplanes
in an application, goes in the right direction.

   So there you have it. Just like Anim-5 -> Anim-7, the use of 32-bit and
not 16-bit optimized code makes a heap of difference. It's a good thought
that no AGA machine has a 16-bit architecture.

