Cant you already see it? Frontier has not been beta-tested. How else
that stack size shit, bulletin board bugs and few other
very obivious mistakes would have been in the release version?
(belive or not, ran from original disks it doesn't run on some
machines, but when you manually set the stack to 100000 it works
fine.)
Also the manual and the game differ very very much when we are
talking about ship stats. Funniest thing is the Panther clipper:

TOTAL MASS (fully loaded): 1775t
CARGO CAPACITY: 2000t

Oh well, the whole ship weights 1775t with full cargo load and all, but
it can carry 2000t? and more funny things: manual states:

TOTAL MASS (fully loaded): 2500t
CARGO CAPACITY: 2100t

leaving nice 400t for the hull and other tidbits, just like in all other
crafts.

Manual also has other bugs and in the last page THEY HAVE EVEN SPELLED
THE NAME OF THE PROGRAMMER WRONG! 

HOW CAN A BETA-TESTER WITH HALF-A-BRAIN AND OVER 5 MINUTES OF PLAYING
TIME MISS SOMETHING LIKE THIS. First time I saw panther clipper in 
ship sales list, I viewed it and started to wonder which one was wrong,
my calculator and brain, or the game's stats!

Also no beta tester could have passed the ship repair 'feature' which requires
you to click mouse/press button for EVERY DAMN 0.25t of hull you repair,
yes, that means 400 t of hull damage = 2400 CLICKS! Auto repair
helps of course, but if you don't want to spend 40t of cargo space
to a non-essential system, you have to buy it, fly out, wait for repair,
go back in, sell it... not logical.

Oh, I'm having good time flaming, lets continue. How about the combat?
After 20-30hrs of gameplay you can have so good ship that you don't need
to fire a shot, just let the enemy crash your shields. And if you want
to fight anything bigger than Imperial Courier, you need to go after
them (killing missions or plain piracy with hyperdrive cloud
following) and when they are not aggressive to you in the beginning,
toasting them to bits with 100MW beam or better is total bore, they
have no chance what so ever.

Missions? Standard stuff found in bulletin board is bore. Shipping
persons or filling out missin persons stuff is clearly
NOT WORTH THE TIME SPENT. (not to mention cargo space,
5t/cabin makes me laugh. I carry robots or slaves instead, better profit)
Killing missions are better but due to the fact that most targets
are just sitting ducks it's also just race against the clock to
get there , do the kill, exit fast and collect payment. No challenge.

Military stuff is MEGAboring in the beginning, just shipping shit. Assasination
missions are mildy interesting, as targets are usually many lightyears
away, and you need to plan the route to get there in time, and it
clearly affects your military rank (*which I PRAY brings you something
like unique missions/additional equipment)

With a standard 3d-routine and just few thousand non-detailed
star systems this would be piece of shit. With MEGA-good (too bad
it's bit power-hungry) 3d-routine and 100 billion starsystems
(ok, 99.9999% are non-interesting) and some good ideas
it is still a good game but WHAT A WASTE of great 3d/starsystem
thing this is. I would go totally crazy if you could map the
unknown starsystems, receive credit for just the mapping (rank/cash)
and have a good chance of actually finding something unique. (something
like find ancient ruins/alien races/ancient damaged spacecraft etc
etc possibilities are endless) And those unique findings should happen
at least 1-2 times /few hours so they would come not too often but
at the same time you would stay hooked as you would wonder what you
find next. 

Currently I'm afraid that one can suck Frontier dry of anything
worth playing in just a few days and the only thing that makes
you to load it again is the spectacular 3d-routine. 
(even it has it's bugs, but I've learnt that with 3d-routines you
have to draw a line how perfect it is and how fast it is. One must
cut corners to make it run more than 1fps)

I reserve my right to change this opinion in case I find
something good from Frontier, but currently
it's going nowhere. I'm going to play it until i'm ELITE,
so i'm sure I won't miss anything...

- Jarnis

