	I've been playing this game for a couple days and thought I
would share some bugs and maybe spoilers...

BUGS:

	First, autopilot is great, but I noticed that it tends to crash
into planets in groups. For example, I might go all day without crashing,
and then spend an hour crashing into everything that moves. Also noticed
that there is a tendency to crash into the same planets over and over again.

	Also, the enemies appear to arrive at predestined intervals. I
can't remember the number of times I had a conflict at x.xxx AU's from
a planet, to the exact number, 10 times in a row or more.

	Only once have I fought more than one enemy at a time.

	Sometimes it says "You arunder attack", and the enemy either
never attacks or isn't even in range as if it doesn't exist.

	Never received help from the "My ship is broken down" or
"My ship is under attack" no matter where I tried it (even near stations).

	If you are at a planet and want to dock on a city on the
opposite side, it IS possible to use autopilot to ck successfully.
I have done this many times.

	Some ports, such as Hoopertown, do not allow me to take off.

	Sometimes taking off using the fastest time mode will launch 
you and state that your time has expired and you must reapply, but send
you out anyway.

	Stations do not appear to be facing planets anymore like Elite I.

	Enemy missiles are rarely to be feared. They are not very 
threatening. And they seem to also leave a smoke trail.

	Attacking a port based on a planet may cause instant death. :)

	Attacking an orbiting stations is hard (I still use 5MW BEAMS).
They appear to have shields. Some stations send out the cops, while others
just fine you forever.

	If you sell goods through the bulliten board, one might be a cop,\
but the other generally isn't if another is listed.

	Sometimes the bullitens request an item for a huge sum, but by
the time I hop skip and jump, they are no longer offered for sale!

	I am also sick of these kamikazee fighters that keep crashing my 
ship as if on purpose.

	In Elite, sometimes you get attacked right after a hyperspace.
Hasn't happened yet in Frontier.

SPOILERS COMING NEXT:











SPOLIERS:

	If you see abig fight coming, set a close hyperspace jump in case
you need to save your butt at the last minute.

	Fast way to make money is to run drugs. For example, buy in
70 Osomething (-1,-1 I think) and trade at Arcturus stations. You will
make 600-700 CR per sale. 

	Look for people offering parcels for high amounts. Grab
as many as you can. Always ask for more money and advanced payment.
If you have no money and are just starting out, just blow them off
and you'll get yopur money to invest anyway.

	When you are up against some enemies, you can set them as
a target and then turn on autopilot. If you are lucky (probably 
dependent on your actual speed), your crosshairs will line up
with the bad guy. In most cases you might also crash, so turn away at 
around .5km by changing to manual control. Some bad guys (lie the
fighter planes) avoid you on their own.

	When an enemy first appears, use Manual control. As you get
your scanner, turn engines off and you can aim much better. Try
to shoot the bad guys while they are turning or flying towards or
away from you. Also good to hit them when they swing close to your ship.
But with engines off, you are a sitting duck for some missiles and
all the guys with beam lasers, so try varying or reserving it for
later in a fight.

	If you want to take a big chance to get more cargo space,
sell your missiles, scanner, atmosphere protector, and possibly
your laser and autopilot. You will not be able to land on some
planets, and you will have trouble fighting, but you can sell
drugs faster. :)

	Here is what I usually trade at best prices: Narcotics, Robots,
Computers, Fruits and Vegetables, Animal Meat. Sometimes Luxury
Goods. All are often featured by people willing to pay double
market value (also battle weapons). Watch out when you trade
illegal items though... the cops might get you.

	Using the fastest time setting increaes the chances of hitting
a planet or of encountering an enemy. Sometimes I set it to one speed
lower to avoid a troublesome bad guy.

	When you really want to threaten people, buy lots of shields
and a beam gun and a quick laser regenerator and go look for fights.
Practice on the police if you want, but they come out in one big
group which is a problem.

	Work your way up to larger ship tonages as quick as possible,
even if it only leaves you with under 3000 CR. I made it to my 5th
ship in one day (70t or so), even after screaming at the game a million
times due to all the kamikazees and autopilot crashes.

	To fight without a scanner, find the bad guy as quick as
possible and select him as a target. then turn the names of the planets off,
and he will be easier to identify. Also, you may get hints from the
system as to which direction the target is in (meager as they are).

	That's all for now...


	
