This message is 100% flames to the coder(s) and publisher of Frontier
(others may want to wear asbestos too, this is really hot stuff)

Feel free to disagree, and if you want, do so in public,
but stay behind your comments when you have uncovered the
truth...

I FEEL CHEATED - FRONTIER IS JUST A PIECE OF SHIT COVERED
WITH ONE OF THE COOLEST DRESSINGS EVER. PERIOD.

After going thru the game file (reading all the texts there
is to read etc) I can say that after you own a 500t+ ship
and you have enough cash to do what ever you want, there is
NOTHING left.

(few military missions and experimenting with totally profitless
mining, but I'll skip those, they are not worth mentioning
for reasons stated later)

Ok, galaxy looks HUGE. But it's just smokescreen. In reality
there is NOTHING beyond the area of the starmap supplied
with the game which covers microscopic area of the whole
galaxy. Nothing in the game file indicates that there would be
anything unique outside say 50-100ly from sun, and even those
randomly generated spaceports end around 200ly. - and galaxy
is HUGE, thousands of light years wide. (hell, tens of
thousands, maybe over hundred thousand, but it's irrelevant)

Those simple and boring missions you can see in the bulletin
board are all you can get - most of them are profitless
and all of them are unintersting after you've done them once. no
challenge what so ever.

Trading - that's something you can do, but you can do it even
in FOFT - and without anything else it gets very booooring
in no time. If you find trading interesting, say that
again after you got 200t or so free cargo space and enough
weaponry to kill anything in less than 10 seconds.

Killing pirates - space combat. Has some idea until you get beam
lasers. After that each battle lasts approx 5-10 seconds. Less if
you have enough shields to ram any enemy. In other words
nothing to do after few hours.

Military missions - you can move stuff (data cards etc) from one place 
to another, get assasination missions (pretty much like those
killing jobs in normal board), get filming missions and even
missions to destroy some installation with nuclear missile.
- AND THATS IT, all missions are same random shit and they offer
no challenge what so ever after 1-2 times done.

Mining. IF you ever land on a planet with no spaceports manually, tell me!
Mining is something I have not been able to try, but then again you
can mine ridiculous amount of 10 tons/miner. You make more profit
with plain trading anyday.

And what else is there? Ship upgrading is exciting for first few hours
of gameplay, but as there is no hidden items anywhere to be found
(well hexdump does list class 4 military drive and 'fighter launcher',
but I belive fighter launcher is not implemented as there is no
other references to it.) after 10-30 hrs depending on your skill
you have maxed your ship.

So all you are left with is to wander around the 100 billion stars that
are out there - with no chance what so ever to find anything ever.

Granted, 3D routine rules - never before has someone succeeded this well
in duplicating at least remotely realistic spaceflight, but there
is simply no substance. With totally lame&easy space combat there
is no real reason to go for ELITE status, as there is nothing out
there.

GO DIG BRABEN OUT OF HIS HOLE AND FORCE HIM TO ADD GAME TO THIS
GREAT 3D ROUTINE!

The bug-farm that is living in the game certainly doesn't help,
there is at least 5 major bugs affecting the gameplay and
few dozen illogicalities, typos and clear spots for
improvements.

So to put it short:

Currently Frontier contains no game beyond few hours of fun, hell 
I find ORIGINAL Elite more intersting after all these years simply
because it has working space combat which requires skill.

- Jarnis (overpissed. cheated. wasted 250FIM for 20-30 hrs
          of fun with nothing left when the game promised
          oh so much)

Please post your followups, let the people hear what you think too.

