Oh my, oh my...

(No re-flame - Just another point of view)

Well, I will not get my hands on Frontier until monday, so I can not
(yet) back my remarks with hours of playing, but :

ELITE *never* offered any challenge beyond the same firts 10-30 hours
of playing!!!

Combat was too easy (When You had built an Iron-ass, mind You).
Trading got boring.
Mining - don't even mention it
Where were all the space-dredgers mentioned in the manual ?
Did anyone ever find the Black Wheel ?


Why did I go on then ? Easy! The freedom of choice. *I* created the
game - not Mr. Braben.

If You (as me) are born about 300 Years to early in the socalled
spaceage, ELITE is one hell of a compensation!, and I expect FRONTIER
to be even bigger - not because of what David Braben put into the
game, but because of what I can get out of it!

Keep in mind that FRONTIER has been hyped for at least a year now -
It simply has to be a let-down if You want Mr. Braben to make it all
happen.


FRONTIER seems to offer a even greater 'universe' with even more
options for a space-jock (Hell, I plan on finding out all I can about
The Federation and The Empire before choosing sides - and then I'm
going to stick with that side until some bastard gets lucky one
evening and catches me off guard in alien skies.)


For me it's going to be another adventure (and I thank David Braben
for giving me that chance).

