In article <2a79k9$b93@mits.mdata.fi>, Jarno Kokko writes:

> Anyway, anyone else got up to average/asp explorer yet?

Me,  and  I'll tell you how.  Right now I'm competent/constrictor, having 4
millions of money left.

You start at Ross 154 system and sell *everything* you have except the auto
pilot.  You don't need missles, or weapons, nothing.  Then you start off to
Barnards  Star, there you land in Boston Base (you should never try to land
on a planet - you sold your Atmospheric Shielding, right?).  Now buy Robots
and  Computers  as much as you can afford/carry.  Then fly to Sol, and land
at  Mars  High.   Here  you  look  at  the Bulletins for people looking for
Computers/Robots.   If  there's  nobody  interested, fast-forward the whole
day  -  next  day's  bulletins  are different.  You'll earn about $1200 per
tonne,  since  people  from the Bulletins pay twice the regular price.  Now
buy  Luxury Goods.  Take them back to Boston Base at Barnards Star and sell
them  normally,  earn about $200-$300 per tonne.  Repeat this until you can
afford a larger ship.  Finally you end up with the Puma or Panther Clipper,
making more than a million per flight.

Note  well,  you will *never* become attacked on this route, as long as you
don't transport sensible small packages from suspicious persons :-)

If  you  feel  you  have enough money for the next few virtual years, buy a
Constrictor.   Equipt it with Auto Refueler, Auto Pilot, A.Shielding, Naval
ECM,  Class  3  Military  Drive,  2  Shield  Generators, Radar Mapper, Hyp.
Analyser,  and a 4MW Beam Laser front mounted.  If I didn't forget anything
you should have 29 tons cargo left for military fuel.  With this equiptment
you  can  follow enemies (removal jobs), win nearly all fights (see below),
fly large distances without refueling (several jumps, 15 light years each),
survive energy bombs with none or 1 tonne damage, and so on.  Excellent.

Now  look  at  the bulletins, people want you to fly small packages to some
systems.   Do  only the $1000+ ones, since they automatically lead you into
trouble.   The  more  trouble  you are in, the more enemies you kill.  Your
Elite ranking raises.

For  fighting,  one  easy  technique  makes  fights  a play for kids.  When
someone  starts attacking you, turn off autopilot and accelerate as much as
you  can.  Turn around your ship that the enemy is behind you.  Look at the
rear view and select the enemy as target.  When you're around 10km far away
from him, turn to front view and enable the autopilot.  Now shoot until the
other  ship  is 3km near, then toggle back to manual control and accelerate
(not  changing  direction).   The  enemy  starts  shooting  at  around  2km
distance,  but  can hardly hit you in manual mode.  Repeat this when you're
again 10km far away from him.  This way takes some time (maybe 5 approaches
average),  but you lose only 1 out of 25 fights (save everytime you dock on
a starport/space station).  And you don't have to train fighting..

That's my whole secret up to now.  Have fun!

