I just downloaded the frontier demo for MSDOS and compared it to the
Amiga demo.  The sequence of pictures in the two demos are exactly
identical.

The only big difference I noticed right away was the texture mapping.
I really like the way the galaxies were done in the PC version.  On
the Amiga you just have those blue patches, the PC version offers a
much more interesting background.  The buildings also looked quite
nice, but as a whole, the texture mapping makes things look a little
fuzzy at times.  For example those building look just like a jumble of
pixels when they overlap each other.  The problem is that the texture
mapping eliminates the sharp edges.  For those who have no idea what
texture mapping is, in the Frontier demo the main texture mapping seen
consists of a lot of small grey strips in various grey colors (makes
it look somewhat like a stone surface).  On the enemy ships the
texture mapping looks quite bad.  They look like they were carved out
of stone...  There was practically no variety in the texture mapping.
Only the building had a somewhat different texture mapping which
actually made them look quite real.

I did not have any sound on the PC version, the internal speaker is
not supported.

Speed-wise the Amiga seemed to be doing a little better.  I ran the PC
demo on a 33MHz 486DX and the Amiga demo on a 28MHz 040 (Amiga 500).
The PC version isn't perfectly smooth.  Sometimes the frames seem to
jump back and forth just a tiny bit (like the camera is shaking).  I
noticed a frame rate slowdown when the big space ship approach right
at the end.  This slowdown was not noticable on my Amiga 500.

The color problem does not exist in the PC version, I guess because it
has 256 colors available.  However the graphics _are_ identical.  I
didn't notice any more colors being displayed on the PC version, just
the color swapping is eliminated.  The PC version uses the same low
resolution the Amiga version does (which looks quite awful on the very
sharp NEC monitor I am using on the 486...  on a 1084 things look a
little less jagged).

That's about it.  I believe there is no reason to be jealous for
either side.  They look very much the same.  The texture mapping has
its nice features, but can be annoying, too.  Also it might be the
reason for the somewhat less perfect animation on the PC.

The PC version has several files associated with the demo, but came to
about the same file size as the Amiga.

Stefan

