  The exit patch recently posted works fine, but there is still a
major problem left: Frontier doesn't use OwnBlitter() (or any other
blitter arbitration protocol). If a background program (fx TrapDoor)
outputs something to screen, there is a good chance of a bad blit.
This won't cause just messed up graphics - it will crash the machine.

  It would be nice if 'frontierpatch' fixes this one, too. An easy
solution is to insert OwnBlitter() in the init routine and
DisownBlitter() in exit. This would block any other blitter using
task, but it's better than nothing.

