RIGHT THEN! I FINALLY have this game, and, as I hoped, I can begin to set some of
our 'bug-spotters' right.
FIRSTLY:
THE DREADED LOCKED SPEED VECTOR!!!
I dont know if I have ever come across this bug in truth, but there is a very
simple phenomenon which could explain most of what has been reported. Ladies,
Gentlemen, Neutered Aliens, please look at your speed indicator more closely.
THRILL as, when you reach a high speed in Km/h, it switches to Km/sec!
GASP as you realise that the reason the damn thing takes so long to change is
that it is now showing a unit of speed 3600 times greater! (yes spacecraft can do
some massive speeds, but it takes a LONG while to slow down!) Another thing to do
is- REMEMBER TO TOP UP THAT INTERNAL FUEL TANK. You will get nowhere fast without
engines.
THE "I HAVE TO CLICK THE MOUSE FOR EACH 0.25T OF HULL DAMAGE" FLAW:
Please examine the desk/table/floor at/on which you play the game. You will
notice an object referred to as the KEYBOARD (ooooh!). This device incorporates a
system called AUTO-REPEAT. Therefore, use the keyboard to operate the repair
screen (I haven't found this in my manual yet, mind you. Press the number key
corresponding to the option you wish to pick, eg if REPAIR HULL is the 4th
option, press and HOLD the 4 key. As an aside, this works for most such choices-
I dont know about the screens with more than 9 options)
THE AUTO-PILOT:
Remeber how much cheaper and yet more versatile this is than the original Docking
Computers. It is not MEANT to be infallible. I find, however, that it is pretty
good if time is set to maximum acceleration- then it usually snaps to realtime
just as it gets docking clearance. Other posts have dealt with this in greater
depth, so I wont harp on, but do realise that if you can see yourself about to be
embedded in the station, switching the A.P. off, then on again will normally save
you (it chickens out every time) As a final word on this one, save often. It
can't hurt, and you may have cause to regret it if you don't.
I think thats enough for now....
