> Basically, targetting a ship manually is nigh on impossible, especially
> if it's small. It's much easier to point in roughly the right direction,
> and let the autopilot line it up properly, then let rip with the guns.

   It's very easy - switch off the Elite-style control emulation, reverse
the up/down direction and then chase after objects with the mouse. Also, as
the manual suggests, switching off the engines helps - you don't end up
being pushed towards objects that you are trying to fire at.

   I thought that the controls [especially the speed controls] were
particularly badly laid out until I worked this out. It would be better
though if you could toggle a "ship control" mode rather than having to hold
down the right mouse button. Also mouse movements should represent
acceleration rather than movement in a given direction, so that you don't
have to keep scuttering around with the mouse to follow things.

   The only trouble is that space combat then becomes trivial, even when
fighting a number of big bastard ships at the same time.

Dave


