Well I have three bugs, which I think haven't been reported yet.
BUT since one of them could seriously spoil your enjoyment of
this great game, I will suggest a couple of improvements first, 
and get back to the bugs later...

(1) Trading in illegal goods.
Frontier is a game all about money, so the wise player will use
any means available to become rich. one of these is smuggling.
Problem: The fine of 2500 c is far to low. With a big ship and 
lots of hot goods, this will be a drip in the ocean. Also you
can break the law a zillion times, but as long as you pay your
fines, everything is fine (get it:-).
Solution: Increase fines or put a reward on the criminal. This
would be cool, with booty hunters all over the galaxy looking 
for you. It would also be a ranking in itself, like the old 
outlaws in the wild west. 

(2) Space combat
Problem: Too difficult in the beginning, too easy when you get
big ships, and "space combat, what is that?" when you get huge
ships. 
Solution: Bigger better (and more) opponents. So what about those 
with tiny ships being attacked by larger (or several) opponents. 
Well, surrender (ie. surrender over radio and jettison all cargo),
or outrun the larger (and slower) opponents. Also the manual 
mentions something about turrets on bigger ships. I think the 
whole idea about fixed guns is stupid. It is a fighter thing, and
2000 ton vessels shouldn't need to turn around to fire. So turrets
should be on any ship which requires a crew (it would explain them 
too). Crew members could fire independently, get a hit accuracy and
be fired or kept on this basis. The Plasma guns should be kept spinal 
mounted. So what is left for you the pilot? Either you can take over
a turret and blast away, or you could fire missiles, set targets 
(which you gunners would fire at), take evasive action, etc etc.
Now think about it: A heroic plunge towards the Phanter Clipper, 
avoiding all fire and delivering a fatal blow to it (hull < 20%),
and then demanding their surrender, yess yess. 
And those opponents should get some training!!! I once fired my gun
on a surface starport. I watched 4 vipers crash into the ground as
they tried to blast me, and I NEVER EVEN MOVED.


Now to the bugs:
(I have a A4000/40, and all of these happen every time i run it)

(1) When launching from Kohl City (Umicron Eridian [2,0]) you get
no thrust and never leave the ground. You can't dip your nose 
upwards as you have height 0, only turn around. And after a long 
time you explode. This happens every time, but I haven't seen it 
anywhere else. A work around is to speed the game up max when 
launching. 

(2) Has anyone been able to lock onto Pluto in the Sol system map.
It never shows any name, just an empty space in the orbital circle.
If you try to click on it, it never centers. Same problem in other
systems (mostly objects in far orbit).


